e, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Of,, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1410–":"about 1410–Deceased","1406–Male":"1406–Deceased","1432–Male":"1432–Deceased","1410–Female":"1410–Deceased","Abt 1410":"about 1410","Abt 1432":"about 1432","Abt 1431":"about 1431","1410":"1410","1432":"1432","1406":"1406","Of,, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Of,, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Corbet","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Corbett  .","History: Walter Corbet, a royal knight in 12th-century Scotland, was the first of that name in that kingdom. His 13th-century descendants were major landholders in the Borders, and in the 14th century they acquired lands in the North of Scotland."],"variants":[{"name":"Corbett","meanings":["English (West Midlands, of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>corbet</i> ‘raven’, probably denoting someone with dark hair or a dark complexion.","History: This is the name of a family descended from Hugh <i>Corbet</i>, a Norman baron who settled in Shropshire following the Norman Conquest. One of his descendants, Sir Richard Corbet, was granted land near Shrewsbury in 1223; since the 13th century, this place has been known as Moreton Corbet. The name was taken from Shropshire to Scotland in the 12th century and to northern Ireland in the 17th century, and thence to North America by at least one group of bearers of the name."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs- Peter Corbet was born about 1410, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Peter ( Poyntmaker) Corbet about 1431, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1410–":"umbes 1410–Surnud","1406–Male":"1406–Surnud","1432–Male":"1432–Surnud","1410–Female":"1410–Surnud","Abt 1410":"umbes 1410","Abt 1432":"umbes 1432","Abt 1431":"umbes 1431","1410":"1410","1432":"1432","1406":"1406","Of,, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1410–":"noin 1410–Kuollut","1406–Male":"1406–Kuollut","1432–Male":"1432–Kuollut","1410–Female":"1410–Kuollut","Abt 1410":"noin 1410","Abt 1432":"noin 1432","Abt 1431":"noin 1431","1410":"1410","1432":"1432","1406":"1406","Of,, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of,, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1410–":"environ 1410–Décédée","1406–Male":"1406–Décédé","1432–Male":"1432–Décédé","1410–Female":"1410–Décédée","Abt 1410":"environ 1410","Abt 1432":"environ 1432","Abt 1431":"environ 1431","1410":"1410","1432":"1432","1406":"1406","Of,, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Of,, Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs- Peter Corbet est née environ 1410, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Peter ( Poyntmaker) Corbet environ 1431, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. 